fields.title: Airbus
fields.description: Airbus SE is a European multinational aerospace corporation. The company's primary business is the design and manufacturing of commercial aircraft. The company also has separate commercial, defence and space and helicopter divisions. Since 2019, Airbus is the world's largest manufacturer of airliners as well as the leading helicopter manufacturer.

fields.title: Boeing
fields.description: The Boeing Company is an American multinational corporation that designs, manufactures, and sells airplanes, rotorcraft, rockets, satellites, telecommunications equipment, and missiles worldwide. The company also provides leasing and product support services. Boeing is among the largest global aerospace manufacturers; it is the third-largest defense contractor in the world based on 2020 revenue and is the largest exporter in the United States by dollar value. Boeing's stock is a component of the Dow Jones Industrial Average.

fields.title: Airbus A330
fields.description: The Airbus A330 is a wide-body, twin-aisle commercial passenger aircraft manufactured by Airbus. It is a versatile and popular aircraft used by many airlines worldwide for long-haul flights. The A330 comes in several variants, including the A330-200, A330-300, and the newer A330neo (New Engine Option).

fields.title: Airbus A340
fields.description: The Airbus A340 is a wide-body, long-range commercial passenger aircraft manufactured by Airbus. It was designed to compete with other long-haul aircraft, such as the Boeing 747, and is known for its extended range and passenger comfort. The A340 family includes several variants, with the A340-200, A340-300, A340-500, and A340-600 being the most well-known.

fields.title: Airbus A350 XWB
fields.description: The Airbus A350 XWB (Xtra Wide-Body) family of aircraft was officially launched in December 2006. The first flight of the A350-900, the initial variant, took place on June 14, 2013. The A350-900 entered commercial service with Qatar Airways on January 15, 2015.
